## Vue 3 and Composition API Best Practices
- Use the Composition API and declarative programming patterns; avoid the Options API.
- Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
- Ensure each file starts with `<script setup>` followed by the `<template>` tag.
- Use **ref**, **reactive**, and **computed** for reactive state management.
- Prefer `defineProps` and `defineEmits` for prop handling and event emission.
- Use `provide/inject` for dependency injection where appropriate.
- Extract reusable logic into composables (`useXYZ.ts`).
- Keep template logic clean and minimal—move logic into the script section.

## Component Structure
- **Script block first**: Always place `<script setup>` block at the top of the component
- **Template second**: Template block comes after the script
- **No scoped styles**: Do not use `<style scoped>`, use Tailwind CSS classes instead

## Script Block Rules
- **Use TypeScript**: Always use `<script setup lang="ts">`
- **Empty script blocks**: If no logic needed, still include empty `<script setup lang="ts">` block
- **Props interface**: Define props with TypeScript interfaces when needed

## Template Rules
- **No IDs**: Do not add id attributes to elements unless specifically required
- **No data attributes**: Do not add data-name or similar attributes
- **Tailwind classes**: Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively for styling
- **Tailwind preferences**: Use standard Tailwind classes (e.g., `w-30`) instead of arbitrary values (e.g., `w-[120px]`)

## Example Component Structure
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
// Props, composables, and logic here
</script>

<template>
  <div class="tailwind-classes-here">
    <!-- Component content -->
  </div>
</template>
```

## Component Naming
- Use PascalCase for component file names
- Components are auto-imported from `resources/js/components/`

## Performance and Optimization
- Use lazy loading and dynamic imports for large components.
- Avoid unnecessary reactivity—use `computed` instead of `watch` where possible.
- Minimize DOM manipulations; avoid v-if inside loops if v-show can be used.